        ('5f8161b6-6c43-4aa6-8812-ad7020230493', '2021-07-18', null, 'Incorrect date of death data for Scotland and the UK', 'Because of an error in the Scotland open data feed, deaths data within 28 days of a positive test by date of death are incorrect for the UK and Scotland - including Scottish local authorities. The issue affects the entire time series, and will be resolved in the next update.

Data for deaths within 28 days of a positive test by publish date are unaffected.', 'Number of deaths by date of death for Scotland are incorrectly recorded as zero for the entire time series. This means that the data for the UK only include England, Northern Ireland, and Wales.', '52f2fd0a-a6ad-45b1-bb0b-2ed7c9933acf', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^S92000003$,utla::^S.*$,ltla::^S.*$}', '2021-07-18 15:39:27.805668'),
        ('d94786c9-3f18-4ac8-9b2d-60ed0575357f', '2021-07-19', null, 'UK newly reported 1st dose vaccinations affected by reduction in Northern Ireland total', 'The total number of 1st dose vaccinations reported in Northern Ireland was lower than the previous day. This means that the number of new first doses given in the UK is reduced by 16,162. The number of new first doses      reported for England, Scotland and Wales combined is 34,348.', '', '52f2fd0a-a6ad-45b1-bb0b-2ed7c9933acf', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^N92000002$}', '2021-07-19 13:04:12.806256'),
        ('433b3d2e-34a5-4e3f-898a-4d9deae680d3', '2021-07-20', null, 'Northern Ireland deaths with COVID-19 on the death certificate not included in UK total', 'Due to a bank holiday in Northern Ireland on 12 July 2021, data for deaths with COVID-19 on the death certificate for the week ending 9 July 2021 in Northern Ireland are delayed. The UK weekly number for week ending 9 July presented on the dashboard is the number registered in England, Scotland and Wales only.
      
Data for Northern Ireland will be added in the next update on Tuesday 27 July. The UK totals for week ending 9 July will be updated at that time.', '', '52f2fd0a-a6ad-45b1-bb0b-2ed7c9933acf', false, false, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^N92000002$,utla::^N.*$,ltla::^N.*$}', '2021-07-20 14:57:29.806652'),
        ('a58e8adc-e1c6-4d85-8d7a-9dc08fa51383', '2021-07-20', null, 'Historical PCR tests added to total figures', 'PCR tests from pillar 1 in England and the UK reported from 20 July 2021 include tests carried out within NHS Trusts that host a PHE lab. 

28,214 historical test samples dating from November 2020 onwards have been added to the total figure.', '', '97ea40d6-c87f-4955-87f6-5eefd60bc5aa', false, false, '{nation::^E92000001$}', '2021-07-20 12:39:27.807028'),
        ('dbad8606-d950-4468-9373-b35f1436437a', '2021-05-21', null, 'Change to reporting of daily new cases in England', 'The way cases are reported in England has changed. Reported cases are sometimes removed if subsequent tests are negative. This happens when cases identified through a positive rapid lateral flow test are followed by polymerase chain reaction (PCR) tests within 3 days that are all  negative. These cases are now being removed daily.

Because of this, the number of newly-reported cases may not be the same as the difference between the total number of reported cases from  one day to the next. The number of newly-reported cases in England and the UK is adjusted to take this into account, but the numbers for  regions and local authorities are not adjusted. This means that for regions and local authorities, this figure does not show the actual  number of new cases reported on that date. For analysis of trends in cases within England, use the data on new cases by specimen date  rather than report date. The new cases by specimen date are always adjusted for the whole time series to take account of any changes.', '', '1940b80b-bb38-42c4-9134-0cafe759f652', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^E92000001$,region::^E.*$,utla::^E.*$,ltla::^E.*$,msoa::^E.*$}', '2021-05-21 13:42:46.807544'),
        ('ccd14d27-5e0a-4026-8aa8-424dc1f3297a', '2021-07-22', null, 'Updated population estimates used for vaccination uptake', 'Vaccination uptake for the UK, nations and Scottish local authorities have been updated to use the latest population estimates for mid-2020, published by the Office for National Statistics. 
      
The updated population has been applied to all dates throughout the vaccination programme.', '', '1940b80b-bb38-42c4-9134-0cafe759f652', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^E92000001$,nation::^S92000003$,utla::^S.*$,ltla::^S.*$,nation::^N92000002$,nation::^W.*$}', '2021-07-22 14:07:55.808000'),
        ('c0959ad1-eabe-4f16-9cee-b183025aef34', '2021-07-28', null, 'Changes to cumulative cases and deaths in Scotland', 'Public Health Scotland has improved its COVID-19 reporting process to ensure it provides the most accurate and timely information.

Because of these changes:

- 1,931 duplicate historic cases have been removed. With the addition of 1,179 newly reported cases, the cumulative number of positive cases is reduced by 752 from the previous total.

- cumulative deaths show a one-off increase of 36. These are historic records since reporting began, and are in addition to the 9 newly-reported deaths.

These changes affect the Scotland and UK cumulative totals.', '', '97ea40d6-c87f-4955-87f6-5eefd60bc5aa', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^S92000003$,utla::^S.*$,ltla::^S.*$}', '2021-07-28 14:17:18.808762'),
        ('e35c7193-1855-4586-9a11-9c51b950c7dd', '2021-07-31', null, 'No update to figures for local areas in Scotland', 'Open data feeds from Public Health Scotland were not updated today (31 July 2021). Figures for local areas will be added to the dashboard when available.', '', '52f2fd0a-a6ad-45b1-bb0b-2ed7c9933acf', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,utla::^S.*$,ltla::^S.*$}', '2021-07-31 15:59:46.809140'),
        ('3e80c9b6-ebc5-4669-9e94-80f894e6fd38', '2021-08-05', null, 'Updated population estimates used for rates of cases, hospital admissions and deaths', 'Rates for cases and deaths for nations, regions and local authorities have been updated to use the latest population estimates for mid-2020, published by the Office for National Statistics. 

Hospital admission rates for NHS Regions have been updated to use the mid-2019 population estimates, which are the most current for that geography. 
     
The updated population has been applied to all dates throughout the pandemic.', 'The latest populations used are available to [download](/downloads/supplements/ONS-population_2021-08-05.csv).

An [analysis of the impact of the change in populations](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/covid-19-impact-of-change-to-mid-year-population-estimates-on-case-and-death-rates) has been published.

Case rates at Middle Layer Super Output Areas still use the mid-2019 population estimates, as the mid-2020 estimates for these areas are not yet available.', '1940b80b-bb38-42c4-9134-0cafe759f652', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^E92000001$,region::^E.*$,utla::^E.*$,ltla::^E.*$,nation::^S92000003$,utla::^S.*$,ltla::^S.*$,nation::^N92000002$,utla::^N.*$,ltla::^N.*$,nation::^W.*$,utla::^W.*$,ltla::^W.*$,nhsRegion::^.*$}', '2021-08-05 15:30:55.809887'),
        ('f2a0af7a-83b6-4ed0-ae18-55741000a30c', '2021-08-22', null, 'Vaccination data for Wales no longer reported on Sundays', 'As of 22 August 2021, Public Health Wales will no longer be publishing vaccination data at weekends. This means that there will be no update to the daily figures for Wales on Saturdays and Sundays, and UK numbers have therefore only been updated with data from England, Northern Ireland and Scotland.', '', '97ea40d6-c87f-4955-87f6-5eefd60bc5aa', false, true, '{overview::^K.*$,nation::^W.*$}', '2021-08-22 12:30:01.782692');